To drive Nigeria’s quest for innovation and global competitiveness, experts have called for the promotion of research and development in tertiary institutions.
   
They added that this move would increase the nation’s knowledge base and creativity of the Nigerian youth.
   
Speaking during the commissioning of Bells Clinic Management system (BCMS), Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Jeremiah Ojediran, noted that the country is yet to give research and development the needed investment.  She lauded the school management and New Horizon’s support in birthing the solution. Rahmat added that the app would be improved upon subsequently. [a dunit=2]  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .